6 AS INTRODUCED
7 A Resolution recognizing March 21, 2025, as Rosie the
Riveter Day; and expressing the significance of the
8 role women played in the Second World War.
9
10 WHEREAS, Rosie the Riveter Day is celebrated on March 21 to
11 recognize the part American women played in America's victory in
12 World War II. As the war raged on in the early 1940s, able-bodied
13 men were drafted to fight, and the female population was called upon
14 to support the workforce. These courageous men and women have since
15 gone down in history to be remembered as The Greatest Generation;
16 WHEREAS, in 2017, the United States Congress passed a resolution
17 to mark March 21 as National Rosie the Riveter Day, a day during
18 Women's History Month;
19 WHEREAS, the symbolism of Rosie the Riveter stands for the
20 millions of women who left their homes for factories to keep the
21 country's manufacturing processes going;
22 WHEREAS, during the Second World War, when every able-bodied man
23 was sent to fight for the Allies, the nation's manufacturing leg
24 came to a halt. From heavy machinery to steel mills and freight
