1 port s, every male-dominated industry came short of personnel due to
2 abrupt drafting;
3 WHEREAS, the federal government issued propaganda to encourage
4 women to join the industrial workforce as a patriotic duty during
5 this time. The iconic poster included a woman in a red bandana
6 raising her fist when used to recruit women;
7 WHEREAS, the total number of female industrial workers went from
8 twenty-seven percent (27%) to thirty-seven percent (37%) between
9 1940 and 1945; more than 19 million women held jobs outside of the
10 traditional women's workforce for the first time ever. Rosie became
11 a cultural icon;
12 WHEREAS, the Rosie the Riveter campaign proved to change the
13 nature of women's involvement in the workforce. This resolution
14 acknowledges the vital role played by women during the Second World
15 War.
16 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
17 OF THE 1ST SESSION OF THE 60TH OKLAHOMA LEGISLATURE:
18 THAT this resolution acknowledges the vital role played by women
19 during the Second World War;
20 THAT March 21, 2025, is hereby recognized by the Oklahoma House
21 of Representatives and the State of Oklahoma as Rosie the Riveter
22 Day.
